modules.description: This module enables jQuery-style DOM manipulation, event handling, and animation configuration in OCaml. It operates on jQuery objects (`jquery Js.t`), DOM elements, and JSON data, supporting tasks like dynamic UI updates, form interactions, and AJAX request lifecycle management. Key use cases include handling user input events, animating element properties, and declaratively transforming web page content through method chaining and callback-driven operations.

This module creates and configures sortable UI components using drag-and-drop functionality. It works with DOM elements via Js_of_ocaml and jQuery, allowing structured reordering of items within containers or groups. Concrete use cases include building interactive lists, nested sortable hierarchies, and customizable layouts with visual feedback during drag operations.
